<p>Charlotte's hot-humid climate demands robust HVAC systems capable of handling both high temperatures and moisture control. The ideal HVAC system for Charlotte homes should feature a SEER rating of at least 16-18, with variable-speed compressors that efficiently manage the city's fluctuating seasonal demands. Heat pumps are particularly effective in Charlotte's moderate winter climate, providing both heating and cooling while consuming less energy than traditional systems.</p>

