<p>Newer developments in Ballantyne, Waxhaw, and University City feature modern construction ideal for solar installations, with many homes already incorporating solar-ready electrical panels and optimal roof orientations. The rapidly growing South End and Plaza-Midwood areas see increasing condo and townhome solar installations, often utilizing shared community solar programs. In established neighborhoods like Cotswold and Sharon Woods, homeowners frequently upgrade aging HVAC systems alongside solar installations, maximizing energy efficiency improvements.</p>

